Jamhuri High School has been closed indefinitely after student unrest. Seven students were seriously injured in a brawl inside the school Tuesday night. Some students admitted to hospitals have stab wounds, officials said. The fight broke out after a section of the students protested alleged discrimination on the basis of religion, students say. On Wednesday morning, Nairobi police bosses held a meeting with the school administration before they announced the closure of the school.   Fight broke out after a section of the students protested alleged discrimination on basis of religion.